p.value: Audiovisual materials have not been preserved and may not be available to researchers. Materials not yet digitized will need to have access copies made before they can be used. To request an access copy, or if you are unsure if an item has been digitized, please contact tamiment.wagner@nyu.edu with the collection name, collection number, and a description of the item(s) requested. A staff member will respond to you with further information.

Suggested format for citing materials in a collection: Identification of item, date; United Automobile Workers of America, District 65 Oral History Collection; OH.019; box number; folder number; Tamiment Library/Robert F. Wagner Labor Archives, New York University.
See BobCat, NYU's library catalog (http://bobcat.nyu.edu), for a description of this collection.  Index available in repository.
